SIMPLE: sapient
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sapient
<hw>Sa"pi*ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sapiens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>sapere</ets> to
taste, to have sense, to know. See <er>Sage</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>
<def>Wise; sage; discerning; -- often in irony or contempt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where the <qex>sapient</qex> king⟦br⟧
Held dalliance with his fair Egyptian spouse.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sage; sagacious; knowing; wise;
discerning.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sapiential</ent>⟦br⟧
